				<text>23.5.2.1 ex1 sine series</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
Obtain the half-range Fourier Sine series for the functions
\[f(t) =&nbsp; 1 \hspace{1cm} 0 \leq t \leq \pi \]
<p></p>
Series is
<p>\( \displaystyle{ \sum_{n=1}^\infty} \) [[input:ans1]]</p>
[[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&nbsp;]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[We extend as an odd function, so 
\[ f(t) = -1 \hspace{1cm} -\pi \leq t \leq 0 \]
Therefore we define 
\[ F(t) = 
\begin{cases} 
-1 \hspace{1cm} -\pi \leq t \leq 0 \\
1 \hspace{1.2cm} 0 \leq t \leq \pi
\end{cases}
\]
As \( F(t)\) is an odd function, \(a_n = 0\). Then we have
\[
\begin{align}
b_n &amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \int_{-\pi}^\pi F(t) \sin n t \hspace{0.1cm} dt = \dfrac{2}{\pi}  \int_{0}^\pi   \sin n t \hspace{0.1cm} dt  \\
&amp;= \dfrac{2}{\pi} \left[ - \dfrac{ 1 }{n} \cos n t \right]_0^\pi \\
&amp;= \dfrac{2}{n\pi} ( 1 - \cos n\pi )\\
&amp;= \dfrac{2}{n\pi}( 1 - (-1)^n)
\end{align}
\]
So the half range Fourier sine series is given by
\[ F(t) =\sum_{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{2}{n\pi}( 1 - (-1)^n) \sin n t \]]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
